TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$b=random(2,5,1);
$a=2**$b;
$d=random(2,5,1);
$c=2**$d;

BEGIN_TEXT
Express the equation in exponential form
$BR $BR 
(a) \(\log_{$a} 2 = \frac{1}{$b}\).
$BR
That is, write your answer in the form \(A^B=C\). Then
$BR
\(A=\) \{ans_rule(10) \}, \(B=\) \{ans_rule(10) \}, and \(C=\) \{ans_rule(10) \}
$BR
$BR
(b) \(\log_2\frac{1}{$c} = -$d\).
$BR
That is, write your answer in the form \(D^E=F\). Then
$BR
\(D=\) \{ans_rule(10) \}, \(E=\) \{ans_rule(10) \}, and \(F=\) \{ans_rule(10) \}
$BR
END_TEXT

$ans1 = 1/$b;
$ans2 = 2;
$ans3 = -$d;
$ans4 = 1/$c;

ANS(num_cmp($a));
ANS(num_cmp($ans1));
ANS(num_cmp($ans2));
ANS(num_cmp(2));
ANS(num_cmp($ans3));
ANS(num_cmp($ans4));

